		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>Well, I'm sorry you said you didn't want this to get to flamed so I'll try to be friendly.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>1."Give all plate wearers the 5 percent mitigation that warriors currently have. Even clerics, and give the warrior 5 percent extra mitigation if you feel its warranted." </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Sorry, but how does setting warriors back to totally even footing with all other plate classes fix anything? I do agree that Knights should have a larger mitigation boost over non&nbsp;tanks then they have now, but to keep things BALANCED warriors would definetley need another boost over that.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>2. "Make shields worthy. Let them effect the die , or add in a block skill using a shield. All 3 tank classes should have this skill. Or any plate class bearing a shield should have this bonus. AC alone is a rediculous reason for anyone to equip a shield."</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Considering that Knights can't dual wield and have many nice 1 hand weapons available, there is more then enough reason for them to use a shield based on AC and stat boosts.&nbsp; Warriors have to trade off a lot of DPS and agro to use a shield.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>3."Give knights a weaponshield(parry) type , or furious(riposte) type disc. Set its length and reuse timer according to wich they get."</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Well, looks like SoE is opposed to these type of disciplines being used for tanking purposes(tipt, etc.) and since both Knights have a DA line of spells that does the same thing, probably won't happen.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>4. "Come up with some benefits for both class to make them more viable in groups. I really like the idea of just having them grouped with you raising attack ac and hp. As&nbsp; has recently been noted. Knights was well known to inspire there fellow combatants."</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>This is already the case, found in the spell books of the knights...SKs can boost group ATK and if the paladin isn't giving the group BSS you got other problems.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>5. "Give SKs more of a role. They seem very much in need of some attention compared to there counterpart IMO."</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>SKs seem to have lost the pulling job, so on raids they really just off tank.&nbsp; Paladins are much more desirable thanks to group heals and BSS.&nbsp; So yes I think SKs could use a nice utility boost.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>6. "BALANCE content before you sell it to us. This is the most rediculous thing that I would have to even ask , or say this. Its obvious these encounters need some attention , and are still unbalanced."</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Exactly, if GoD were balanced to start with we would not be dealing with 80% of the issues we are now.</DIV>	
