		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV>I don't mean to flame, you sound like a warrior, but you sound like a warrior who's completely given up on any idea of a definitive role in the game. You're basically offering the hybrids every advantage we have over them and not removing the myriad of advantages they already have over us via their spell books. Warrior should be a superior tank - having content in game that requires the supreme tank is not unrealistic imo. There are plenty of RL examples of where supreme warriors are needed to accomplish a given goal, and where an army fails without the best of the best. There are also myriad fantasy situations where this fits in. I would gladly give up a certain amount of dps in order to retain this goal with which I created my character, but if you want to upgrade the mitigation of hybrids, there should be an equal mitigation upgrade to warriors. The recent upgrade to hybrids by removing the usefullness of warriors in the situations mentioned is imo aggregiously misappropriated, including the fact that this merely opened the doorway to charmed npc tanking. Bring more roleplay back into the game -- don't carbon copy the warrior role into the hybrid role and completely nullify the role of the supreme tank. The hybrids consider this arrogant of course, they think that we are coveting the tank role at all costs, but in reality we chose a class that is entirely a tank class, while they chose a class that is possibly primarily a tank class, and in entirely imaginably secondarily a tank class.</DIV><SPAN><SPAN class=date_text><FONT color=#c0c0c0>06-24-2004</FONT></SPAN><SPAN class=time_text><FONT color=#ffffff>02:00 AM</FONT></SPAN> </SPAN>
<P></P>
<HR>

<P>Indeed I am a warrior. I already have a definitive role in this game. I regularly MT for my guild , and I see none of the changes that I suggested or recommended would change that. I am not offering every advantage we have. We have slightly better itemization. We have better innate hp. We could still have the base 5 percent better mitigation. We would get defensive and our other discs back. Thats two people that preferred to ignore the fact that it is up to the developers if they want to give us 10 percent and plate wearers 5 percent.&nbsp; Zak there are several encounters where knights are preferred tanks. The warping zek comes to mind. Do you think this is wrong? Some of you sound like we should be the only tanks. Paladins and SKs do have some utility , but if you think thats going to give them a role your sadly mistaken. I believe knights should be decent tanks, they should not be able to out tank there parent class. How is roleplaying going to balance basic tanking issues? We will remain the supreme tank imo this would just even out the playing field more. One last thing Zak , I am indeed bending here. I do not believe that all of these things I suggested will or would be implemented. They are just ideas to balance out the game to make knight classes a bit more desired at the high end of the game. I dont consider your post a flame , but I see very little it does to help anything. I for one have heard enough of warriors must be the supreme tank , and if we give anything to knight classes we wont be.&nbsp;I believe we are the supreme tank , and even givin them a bit of a upgrade would not change that.</P>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							Katur Carus
Proud leader of
Final Evolution
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
