<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&message.id=1500#M1500">9</a> of 71
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 803 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			Rav, you want knights to get a raid role that doesn't require tanking? THat is purely, utterly, completely, insane.<br><br>There are 3 healing classes in EQ.<br><br>Multiple buffing classes.<br><br>Multiple DPS classes.<br><br>Multiple debuff classes.<br><br>One tank class.<br><br>Oh no, wait, there are 3 tank classes. Now, with that in mind, below are a few suggestions that I dont think will take any roles from warriors that they rightfully deserve.<br><br>Knights DO NOT WANT TO BE BETTER RAID MT'S THAN WARS.<br><br>Yes, its very true. For the majority, at least. I'm not sure what idiot knight is telling you they want to tank raid bosses at the same level warriors can, but whoever it is is smoking crack.<br><br>Knights want two things.<br><br>We want a real raid role. The majority of sk's think, and this goes along with simple logic, that it should be a tank role. Warriors...you can tank raid named, you always do tank raid named, you always have tanked raid named (I wasn't around in Kunark, so no idea about then honestly), this is not going to change, we dont want it to.<br><br>Warriors: Raid MA's.<br><br>Knights: Raid offtanks.<br><br>Whats so wrong with that?<br><br>In all honesty, knights do need to tank better. You can call it a mini-defensive, you can call it a debuff, you can call it whatever you want - but we NEED something.<br><br>The arguement is brought up repeatedly that giving knights a form of miniature defensive would kill warrior's role. How would giving knights a defensive NOT AS POWERFUL as warrior defensive take ANYTHING away from their raid MT role? <br><br>In a hypothetical situation (and this is NOT what we want, just an example) even if knights were to get a carbon copy of Defensive, the same as warriors get, warriors would STILL BE PRIMARY RAID MT'S. You would still have more hp, and better mitigation than us. Still have Furious and AE taunt for tank switches.<br><br>Many people have proposed different solutions, a slow/overhaste tap, a custom defensive, an accuracy debuff, an agility recourse, Fear2, rune increase, etc. etc. The only two of these ideas that simply needs to DIE, is a slow/V3 haste tap and a rune increase. Those simply WILL NOT work. Below are some quotes from me in other threads explaining why these will not work.<br><br>The problem with giving us a "rune" line, is that it doesn't scale at all. The rune may absorb 3000 damage, which will be fine at the beginning of said expansion, but later on it will continue to do less and less, while a stun scales to content. A 3 second stun is stopping the mob from attacking for 3 seconds. On old content, stuns wouldn't be as powerful as a rune thing for us, and on new content, they would still be much more powerful.<br><br>I don't know about anyone else, but I don't spend all my time soloing old world content.<br><br> An overslow will just not be effective.<br><br>We are trying to secure an offtanking role, correct? Yes.<br><br>Now, our main problem is beign able to stay alive through that offtanking, and the brunt of that being the period we tank before clerics target us, get heals off, mob gets slowed, etc.<br><br>I'm sure you will agree, for a slow spell to have any real impact on our survivability in these offtanking encounters, it would have to be at LEAST 20%. And even then the help would be negligible.<br><br>We would then become constant debuff bots. Thats all we would be good for. Paladins and Warriors would still tank completely better than us, and many many encounters would be insanely trivialized.<br><br>95% slow?!?! Can you imagine how that would affect many many encounters already in game?<br><br>Personally, as a ShadowKnight, I picked this class to tank, and be a part of the battle. I did not play a ShadowKnight to be a buff/debuff bot on raids. If I wanted to do that, I would play a shaman.<br><br>20% overhaste (v3) wouldn't be a bad thing for us, I admit, but it would do nothing to balance us, it would be a nifty toy. Your not going to take a SK with you to go through Ikkinz trials because he has 20% overhaste for the group. A Sk is not going to have a viable offtank role in raids because he has 20% overhaste.<br><br>While ideas to balance our tanking that aren't completely defensive-centered are good, they need to be realistic.<br><br>Slein Jinn, whom primarily posts on shadowknight.org, has what seems to me the best solution for shadowknights and paladins alike.<br><br>Before I post a link to his idea for a mini defensive, let me go over where current gaps are in tanking..<br><br>Gap1:Warriors are far far ahead of knights, in single group, main raid tank, and offtanking.<br> We dont want upgrades to all these areas, but we cant be second rate in every single one of them. Warriors can stay raid MT, and knights can be primary offtank. And all 3 tank classes can equally SHARE single groups. I think that is the best solution to that gap. Overview: Knights = Best offtanks, equal to warriors and each other in single groups. Warriors = Best raid MT's, equal to warriors and each other in single groups.<br><br>Gap2: ShadowKnight to Paladin. <br>Because of Stuns, paladins are significantly ahead of ShadowKnight in terms of raid AND group friendliness and tanking ability. ShadowKnights need something to copmpensate for this.<br><br>Gap3: Non-tanking classes to Tanks.<br>This gap is too SMALL. This gap needs to be increased. Knights need an extra 5% mitigation, and warriors need an extra 5% mitigation. It is NOT right that rangers tank as well as they do compared to knights.<br><br>So, what does everyone need?<br><br>Warriors: +5% mitigation.<br><br>Paladins: +5% mitigation, either Slein Jinns proposed custom-tailor minidefensive offtank disc, or one of its equivalent in different form. You can "disguise" it, and yes that is a crude word, as whatever you want, such as my idea for a pet sharing damage with you. <br><br>ShadowKnights: +5% mitigation, either Slein Jinns proposed custom-tailor minidefensive offtank disc, or one of its equivalent in different form. You can "disguise" it, and yes that is a crude word, as whatever you want, such as my idea for a pet sharing damage with you. Something to balance us with paladins, such as an accuracy debuff, Fear2, etc.<br><br>Non-tanking classes: Nothing.<br><br>Relative links:<br>1: My personal idea to balance SK's to Paladins. http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&message.id=1262<br>2: Slein Jinn's proposed mini-defensive to balance knights to warriors and other ideas.<br>http://www.shadowknight.org/forums/showthread.php?t=21880<br><br>Katur, it is nice to see warriors like you who can actually objectively look at the big picture, and not just their own little MUST TANK ALL TEH MOBBERS world.	
		</td></tr>
