<P>Why would you think that I think this is wrong when that's the exact point I was trying to make -- there's a raid where they are necessary, </P>
<P><BR>
<HR>
<BR>Please allow me to prefice this by saying that I play on VZ, a pvp server, and therefor possibly see knights in a different light than the majority of you blueby's. On my server there are NO schedules for raids, NO working with other guilds to figure out on which nights which guilds get which mobs --only the strong survive, and ONLY if we can conquer our enemies first are we allowed a chance to raid.<BR><BR>Therefor, knights are overpowered on my server, there are no complaints from them for balance, because they dominate guild wars and are a major factor ( and gearing them up is a major factor) in wether or not we are capable of raiding on any given night.<BR><BR>So, their role on a raid is not as big of a deal, and I'll admit, my perception of them on raids might not "get along ", as you said, with your perception of them as helpless weakilings who we must support to raise them up to be able to tank all melee named mobs as well as warriors. If this is just a perception issue based on our different views from different servers, then so be it; but warrior nerfs such as the recent one from SoE affect all warriors regardless of server and therefore are even more unbalancing IMO.<BR><BR>I am not upset with the recent warrior nerfs as they affect me directly at this point, but as a wise **SMURF** said during WWII " who will be left to support me when it's my turn", I see this nerf as a startling introduction of a solution to knight complaints. I am not even EP flagged yet --however if they continue this as a precident as you have suggested and use warrior ability's as merely a 5% mitigation bonus, I see my RP value in this game as being seriously undermined.<BR>My guild as I said is not EP flagged, yet we are working toward that, and I find this a much more worthy challenge than joining a time equipped guild and being pathitically backflagged endlessly in order to simply be able to even compete with my warrior bretheren.In addition to your mention of hybrid usefullness on raids as being on the Zek raids, I just tonight did for the first time the HoH trials, and our Knights were incredibly valuable to this raid as were bards and rangers in order to kite the mobs while we one by one picked them off and tanked them (yes, I said tanked as in a warrior held aggro while the clerics CH'd etc. -- all the members did their DPS and not one whined that it was imbalancing that they were left to DPS positions [including the warriors who did not MT any mobs])<BR><BR>On my server hybrids have incredible value, while the warrior class continues to have ONE, and only ONE main function --MT on raids. The only way we can achieve this status is to be in SOME WAY valuable in exp groups, and removing all our usefulleness beyond our 5% (which is pathetic considering we have NO unique defensive AA's) mitigatiuon is seriously considering undermining the warrior population and our roll in Norrath.<BR><BR>Once again this is from a PvP standpoint, and possibly hybrids on easy servers seriously have no role, but when we as warriors (on my server) give all their advantage up in order to tank on raids, and then face the possibillity that our only remaining positon is being undermind, we are understandably upset.<BR>
<HR>
