<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&message.id=1532#M1532">25</a> of 71
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 680 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>Basically, IMHO, the entire combat system needs to be re-written PERIOD. There are inconsistencies across the classes, depending on what zone you're in AC means something totally different, the class definitions have gone out the window, i don't think anyone understands exactly what ATK means in any instance, etc. After they work out the current bugs, get their new expansion out the door, and finalize the guild summit changes... take some time and analyze the current in game systems. Take a step back&nbsp;and look at what you have.&nbsp;I think the base of the combat system is what no one understands/likes. Change the combat system based on the ideas of the community. A lot of the ideas presented in this thread are common sense to me, but just don't apply to game mechanics as is. I understand this would be a lot to ask for, but as EQ evolves, you base systems must evolve. I'm a web-based application programmer, and i'm to the point in my development on a project, where i need to totally revamp a major component of the base system. This is unfortunate, and will take a good couple weeks/months of work, but in the long run, i know what i'm changing it to will work better and make more sense not only to the people using my application, but it will ease my future expansion as well. I think the premise of EQs combat system is in the right place, i just think that EQ has outgrown it. AC/ATK caps have been raised, the gear people are achieving was never even a thought to the original players of EQ, the combat abilities being introduced are well beyond anything the original game intended... etc. Make a system that makes sense to the community and is highly adaptable, and the community will&nbsp;spend time enjoying the game, rather than knit-picking each and every imbalance they perceive.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>-Aeg</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
